headline.main: Cruise of the United States Frigate Wabash.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States steam frigate Wabash, the flag-ship of the Home Squadron, and bearing the broad pennant of Commodore PAULDING, has been in commission about 18 months. Her last cruise occupied seven months, and was an eventful one. She sailed from New-York on the 29th of July, under orders for Aspinwall, with reference to the unsettled state of Central American affairs;

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. Silsbee, the new Mayor of Salem, Mass., has put forth his views touching the Temperance question, greatly to the astonishment of the people, He opposes prohibitory laws, and adds: " I have not only studied this subject at home, but in various nations abroad; and have invariably found those the most temperate where the vine grew best, and where all had the freest enjoyment of its blessings.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the London Times. What is to be the future destiny of the great race which inhabits the opposite shores of the Atlantic ! Springing from the old English stock. and ingrafting on itself schools from every European people, it is advancing with unprecedented rapidity to power and wealth. headline.main: THE MORMON REBELLION.; Origin of the Discontent at Salt Lake--Unwise Appointments by the Federal Government-Excesses of U. S. Troops During their Residence in Salt Lake City in 1854--Determination of the Mormons to Keep out Troops for the Future-Will there be any Fighting?

docs.lead_paragraph: President BUCHANAN is correct, in the statement in his late Message, that there is reason to believe that Gov. YOUNG has long contemplated his present rebellious attitude. To prove this, and give your readers a clearer view of causes that have hastened the rebellion, it will be necessary for me to state, at length, some circumstances preceding the present state of affairs.
